mmetry (<code>a.k.a line of symmetry</code>) is a line that divides a symme=
trical shape into two <strong>congruent </strong>parts. &nbsp;</p><p><img s=
rc=3D"https://www.allmath.com/storage/2023/Oct/axisofsymmetry_76.png" alt=
=3D"axis of symmetry" width=3D"500" height=3D"415"></p><h3><strong><span st=
