strong></span></p><p>Find the Axis of symmetry &nbsp;for <code>f(x) =3D x=
=C2=B2 + 4x =E2=88=921</code></p><p><strong>Solution&nbsp;</strong></p><p><=
strong>Step 1: </strong>Take the given function and find the values of <str=
ong>a </strong>&amp; <strong>b</strong>.</p><p><code>f(x) =3D x=C2=B2 + 4x =
=E2=88=921</code></p><p>In the given&nbsp;quadratic function,</p><p><code>a=
 =3D 1</code></p><p><code>b =3D 4</code></p><p><strong>Step 2: </strong>Tak=
e the formula for the quadratic function and place the values of <strong>a<=
/strong> &amp; <strong>b</strong>.</p><p><code>x =3D -b / 2a</code></p><p>x=
